creator: E. Phillips Oppenheim
description:
LibriVox recording of The Devil's Paw by E. Phillips Oppenheim.
Read in English by Tom Weiss
A beautiful, intelligent young woman – is she a traitorous spy or a patriot? An aristocratic soldier permanently injured during the war – is he a patriot or is there more to him than meets the eye? A clandestine meeting on a beach – espionage or peace movement? (Summary by Tom Weiss)
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

Download M4B (175MB)
subject: librivox; audiobooks;
title: The Devil's Paw

reviews.reviewbody:
Another tale of WWI espionage from Oppenheim and once again we have both an exciting tale and an interesting insight into the minds of the author and his many readers almost a century ago.  As ever feminists and socialists will have to block their ears at some points!

The reader, as usual, does a fine job.
